content.description: Trend right on good holds, climbing above a separated block, through a slight bulge to anchors.
content.location: Immediately right of Unknown 5.6, about 70 feet left of the A-frame roof, just right of the Lil Smokie Does Super Mama chockstone.

content.description: Follow good holds on a vertical wall, straight up to the anchors
content.location: On the extreme left end of lower Psychoactive, about 70 feet left of the A-frame cave, just right of the Lil Smokie Does Super Mama chockstone. Trail and belay stance are steep and prone to erosion.

content.description: Starting from a block, pull a roof and continue above on ok holds.
content.protection: Bolts to an open shut and a bail biner.
content.location: About 50 feet from the A-frame cave, look for a 2 foot roof above a block. Scramble onto the block, but belay from the ground below and to the right of the block.

content.description: The crux comes quick. Reach high for the huge jug, and then quickly figure out how to work the power crux. Once through the business, blast to the top on exceptional pockets before the pump sets in.
content.location: Heading up the trail to Psychoactive Wall (proper), this route climbs the northern face of the prominent, overhanging arete formed by the massive leaning bolder.

content.description: A harder, bouldery start on small pockets and features to more mellow climbing to the anchors. A high first bolt begs to be stick-clipped to protect the crux.
content.location: This is the right-most route of the first wall of Lower Psychoactive. Strangely Compelled (5.11d) is just on the other side of the arete.

content.description: Vertical climbing with thin pockets gives way to bigger holds above the bulge.
content.location: This is the farthest right climb in the Lower Psychoactive area.
On a chock stone on the far left side of the wall.

content.description: Super bouldery start to a long stint of pockets up top.  Definitely stick clip the first bolt.
content.location: The overhanging arete right of the big cave at Lower Psychoactive.

content.description: hard start to jug pulling to easy finish
content.protection: 6 or 7 bolts with drop in anchors
content.location: left boulder of lower psycho, inside cave and looking at the left boulder its the right most line closest to the cave.

content.description: Make difficult moves in a very shallow corner to good holds on a slab. Follow the slab past bolts to the anchor.
content.protection: Bolts. Definitely stick clip the first bolt.
content.location: About 20 feet right of the Tumbleweed Block, or about 30 feet left of the A-frame cave. Look for a very shallow, very open corner.

content.description: Crux right off the ground, so you may want a stick clip. Also doable to clip first from the block on the left if you step off it. Scary slab climbing to second bolt which gradually gets easier as the climb gets less steep. Climb to a ledge in less than ideal dirty holds and shortly after get the anchor.
content.location: To the left of greenie invasion, the bolt line just to the right of the large block.
